HEADWORD: Cullion
<hw>Cul"lion</hw> <pr>(k?l"y?n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF.
<ets>couillon</ets>, <ets>coillon</ets>, F. <ets>co<?/on</ets>, a vile
fellow, coward, dupe, from OF. <ets>couillon</ets>, <ets>coillon</ets>,
testicle, fr. <ets>il</ets> the scrotum, fr. L. <ets>coleus</ets> a
leather bag, the scrotum.]</ety> <def>A mean wretch; a base fellow; a
poltroon; a scullion.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Away, base
<xex>cullions</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

